s clear that the rest of them have aged. While they enjoy their little meet up, it ends sadly as the main hero dies the next day.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eEven more time passes before Frieren sets out on another adventure, reluctantly taking on a protégé. She treks through places she’s seen before, and comes across villages she once saved, only to find she’s a distant memory now now. It’s something that she’s accepted, having already lived for hundreds of years; no matter how legendary, all heroes fade, even when they insist their greatness will spare them this fate.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25349811/frieren4.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0,0,100,100\" data-pswp-height=\"1080\" data-pswp-width=\"1920\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"A red-haired young man in a red coat, a purple-haired girl, and a small elf woman with white hair stare at a group of statues in the middle of a town square. From Frieren: Beyond Journey’s End\" data-chromatic=\"ignore\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"(max-width: 639px) 100vw, (max-width: 1023px) 50vw, 700px\" srcset=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25349811/frieren4.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=256 256w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25349811/frieren4.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=376 376w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25349811/frieren4.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=384 384w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25349811/frieren4.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\